reviews.review: Have you ever cried so hard while watching a movie?

Out of all SPA films, it was a letdown that the animation style of this film won't be the same as the whimsical feel these Sony films have. It had a weakest script, and the basic concept of this film is essentially a clich√©. It tried make something out of it's unoriginality, yet they made nothing new about it. The jokes are simply terrible, to the point that they're just "meh". But out of all of that, it is just nothing but ads that ran for 86 minutes.

Trash. Super bad. Horrible jokes. But the only time I actually laughed was when Jailbreak said "Men are always taking credit for what women do." Still makes me laugh to think that Sony thinks gender inequality is a thing! Ha!

This movie is just so bad. Not even so bad its good. This movie is what you watch when making a movie too see what to avoid. This movies best  use is as a torture device. It hurts to watch. The horrible attempt at morals makes it painful to watch. I can't believe I wasted over a hour of my life. Why Sony? How did 39% of people like this? its just the worst. I could probably make a better movie in five minutes. Overall bad. Just bad. Nothing else. Bad, Bad, TRASH.

This movie was life changing. Really changed my outlook on life. The parents monotoned voice was a little slow at first but at about minute 52 you really started to understand the pain behind those voices. Well deserved these five stars. (:
